‚†Ä
This is a delicious plant-based and vegan gingerbread cake featuring a naturally caramelized peach topping.‚†Ä
‚†Ä üå± @pebblesandtoast üå±  Click the link in my bio for this Ultimate Supreme Pizza recipe and more! üçΩ ‚ì•
 
With Carolina peaches in season this time of year, I just can‚Äôt help myself from making healthy peach treats.  Instead of using a yellow cake base, this upside-down cake features a mild gingerbread cake. I love that this cake contains no butter, oil, eggs, or refined sugar.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
How is this even possible? In short, pure maple syrup, coconut sugar, and applesauce.  These naturally sweet ingredients are wholesome sugar alternatives that lend a natural sweetness and complement this delightful peach dessert.‚†Ä
The end result is simply delightful. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This Peach Upside-down Cake is full of flavor with a substantial yet moist crumb. It‚Äôs great served warm or at room temperature, plain or dressed up with ice cream or non-dairy whipped cream.  It comes with its own light sauce on top.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
