I went out for Thai food on Wednesday and chose a dish called Pad Krapow. It is a tofu stir fry with delicious thai seasoning. After eating I was inspired to try and make it myself üçú 

I think it went pretty well- please see the recipe below üå±‚ù§Ô∏è 

Ingredients:
200 grams of tofu
2 chillis 
4 cloves of garlic
1cm of ginger
2 tablespoon of a neutral oil 
2 tablespoons dark soy sauce.
9-12 Thai basil leaves
A pinch of brown sugar.
1 white onions
1 pepper 
Handful of green beans
Rice to serve

Recipe: 
1. Heat the oil in a wok until it‚Äôs very hot and add the garlic, chilis, and onions. 
2. Cook the tofu for 3 minutes before adding veg. Stir-fry until the vegetables are fragrant(about 20-30 seconds).
3. Add the dark soy sauce and sugar. Stir-fry for a further 20 seconds. 
4. Remove the wok from the heat, put the basil leaves into the wok and stir-fry until they wilt. The leaves typically wilt within 10 seconds maximum. 
5. Serve the stir-fry alongside your rice of choice. (You can also serve with salad and fresh tomatoes).
